OL,5,G```FIMPULS RAPIDPLAYG``````````````````
OL,7,GRunning on a Pentium P233, Fritz5 took 
OL,8,Gthe third place spot with 10/13,       
OL,9,Gdefeating experienced GMs such as      
OL,10,GGulko, Kasinijanov and Beim in the     
OL,11,Gprocess. Fritz5 score at the festival  
OL,12,Gallowed it to turn in a 2700 Elo       
OL,13,Gperformance (rapid).                   
OL,15,FHowever, all was not lost for mankind. 
OL,16,FEqual first place was shared, on       
OL,17,F10\/13, between GMs Igor Khenkin, from 
OL,18,FIsrael, and Joel Benjamin, USA.        
